experience.description:
Review claims and, together with the multidisciplinary team, prepare and review consultancy reports, emphasizing key observations and providing recommendations.

Key responsibilities are: 
- Coordination of the agenda and management of the team meetings:
- Preparation and follow-up of formal communication with clients; 
- Coordination of tasks with multidisciplinary teams; 
- Review and manage the consulting reports at their different stages.

Assisting the Head of Legal. I performed a variety of tasks in the context of an arbitration before the International Chamber of Commerce, for a claim over USD 200 million.

During this period I had the opportunity to continue developing my ability to work with multidisciplinary teams, mostly from different parts of the world, promoting good communication and collaborative work.

I also continued to strengthen my bilingual communication skills. Some of my responsibilities included:

- Handling of confidential information;
- Participation in the coordination and assignment of the arbitration team tasks;
- Review of written submissions and claims;
- Collaboration in the production of supporting documents for the claim;
- Coordination and logistics of arbitration matters (defining meeting points, travel, etc.);
- Participation in the preparation of witnesses;
- Drafting of monthly status reports for the Board of Directors;
- Preparation, negotiation and monitoring of service agreements;
- Preparation and monitoring of change orders, annexes, amendments to contracts;
- Formal communication and correspondence with clients and suppliers;
- Review of Loan Agreements, Memorandum of Understanding;
- Act as a liaison between the company and the different international law firms representing the company;

Assisting the Head of the Contract Administration Department. The Project consisted in the construction of the "Alto Maipo Hydroelectric Power" located in the Andes (Chile); EPC contract value over USD 300M. Part of my responsabilities included:

- Contract analysis and interpretation;
- Reply to the team members queries regarding the contract;
- Assessment and issuance of claim notices to the client, in consultation with the various departments involved;
- Preparation of claim notices updates, including compiling justification in terms of costs and time;
- Preparation of monthly reports regarding the status of the claims;
- Negotiation of subcontracts, maintaining back to back principles in fulfillment witht the main contract;
- Review of all formal letters sent to the client and preparation of draft letters response;
- Monitoring the status and expiration of the Performance Guarantees submitted by the subcontractors;
- Review of the risk matrix, jointly with the client;
- Assist to weekly coordination meetings with the head of departments, updating on latest events, managing follow up tasks and minutes of meeting.

Presentation of patent, utility models and industrial design applications, and brand renewals;
Follow-up of the applicable deadlines;
Direct communication with clients regarding the management and status of the applications; 
Budget and monitoring of annuity payments.

volunteering.description:
Tareas enfocadas en asistir a personas en situación vulnerable:
- Revisión de contratos de trabajo;
- Evaluar tipos de asistencia gubernamental aplicable;
- Asesorar posible representación legal ante causas judiciables;
- Apoyo para la obtención de permisos de residencia, documentos de identidad:
- Orientación sobre cómo acceder a ciertos derechos fundamentales (como ser educación, alimentación y accesibilidad)

